me":"bovil","ctime_ts":1204416188,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/41738927/4545815","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/37559.html?replyto=3571639","name":"reply","title":"Reply","footer":1},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/37559.html?thread=3571639#t3571639","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/37559.html?thread=3571639#t3571639","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/37559.html?thread=3571639#t3571639","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"kevin_standlee","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://kevin-standlee.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":3571639,"talkid":13951,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/37559.html?thread=3571639#t3571639","above":3570871,"upictitle":"Kevin Standlee: Hugo Trophy","article":"I've been reminded that voting for the <a href=\"https://secure.locusmag.com/2008/2008PollAndSurvey.html\">Locus Awards</a> is free (and is going on right now).  You need pay nothing to vote on their awards.  They aren't the Hugo Awards, but they are free.","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"9 years ago","below":3579831,"ctime":"March 2 2008, 00:34:54 UTC","parent":3569847,"massactions":0,"subject":"","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://kevin-standlee.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"kevin_standlee","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"kevin_standlee","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://kevin-standlee.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"kevin_standlee","ctime_ts":1204418094,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/8614504/394220","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/37559.html?replyto=3571895","name":"reply","title":"Reply","footer":1},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/37559.html?thread=3571895#t3571895","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/37559.html?thread=3571895#t3571895","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/37559.html?thread=3571895#t3571895","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"the_magician","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://the-magician.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":3571895,"talkid":13952,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/37559.html?thread=3571895#t3571895","above":3571639,"upictitle":"The Magician: pic#8614504","article":"The <a href=\"http://www.bsfa.co.uk/bsfa/website/awards.aspx\">British Science Fiction Association Awards</a> are being voted on at the moment also ... though there you have either to be a member of the BSFA or a member of the British National Science Fiction Convention a.k.a. <a href=\"http://www.orbital2008.org\">Orbital 2008</a>.<br /><br />To vote for the Oscars you have to be a member of the AAMPAS (I think that's the right abbreviation!) etc.<br /><br />There are very few \"People's Choice\" awards out there. Most awards are either decided by a panel of judges or by members of some society or association, and membership almost always costs money.<br /><br />It's strange how people can go through their whole lives and not realise this, but then there's a bunch of things I don't know and don't know I don't know (e.g. how are the members of the Electoral College selected? Which army  made Mr.Sanders a Colonel? Was there ever a \"small Mac\"? How do you recompile the kernel of an Asus EEE and if it fails halfway through, do you end up with a dead brick or is there some very lowlevel bootstrap?)","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"g